{"key":"content:zh:2.guide:3.directory-structure:6.content.md","generatedAt":"2022-07-12T12:13:02.517Z","mtime":"2022-07-12T12:13:02.507Z","slug":"content","title":"content","position":"000200030006","to":"/guide/directory-structure/content","draft":false,"page":true,"language":"zh","icon":"IconDirectory","head":{"title":"Content directory"},"empty":false,"description":"The Nuxt Content module reads the content/ directory in your project and parses .md, .yml, .csv and .json files to create a file-based CMS for your application.","body":{"raw":"---\nicon: IconDirectory\ntitle: 'content'\nhead.title: Content directory\n---\n\n# Content directory\n\nThe [Nuxt Content module](https://content.nuxtjs.org) reads the `content/` directory in your project and parses `.md`, `.yml`, `.csv` and `.json` files to create a file-based CMS for your application.\n\n::list{type=success}\n\n- Render your content with built-in components.\n- Query your content with a MongoDB-like API.\n- Use your Vue components in Markdown files with the MDC syntax.\n- Automatically generate your navigation.\n\n::\n\n## Get started\n\n### Installation\n\nInstall the `@nuxt/content` module in your project:\n\n::code-group\n\n  ```bash [yarn]\n  yarn add --dev @nuxt/content\n  ```\n\n  ```bash [npm]\n  npm install --save-dev @nuxt/content\n  ```\n\n  ```bash [pnpm]\n  pnpm add -D @nuxt/content\n  ```\n\n::\n\nThen, add `@nuxt/content` to the `modules` section of `nuxt.config.ts`:\n\n```ts [nuxt.config.ts]\nimport { defineNuxtConfig } from 'nuxt'\n\nexport default defineNuxtConfig({\n  modules: [\n    '@nuxt/content'\n  ],\n  content: {\n    // https://content.nuxtjs.org/api/configuration\n  }\n})\n```\n\n### Create content\n\nPlace your markdown files inside the `content/` directory in the root directory of your project:\n\n```md [content/index.md]\n# Hello Content\n```\n\nThe module automatically loads and parses them.\n\n### Render pages\n\nTo render content pages, add a [catch-all route](/guide/directory-structure/pages/#catch-all-route) using the `ContentDoc` component:\n\n```vue [pages/[...slug].vue]\n<template>\n  <main>\n    <ContentDoc />\n  </main>\n</template>\n```\n\n## Documentation\n\n::alert{type=info}\nHead over to <https://content.nuxtjs.org> to learn more about the Content module features, such as how to build queries and use Vue components in your Markdown files with the MDC syntax.\n::\n","ast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"prose-h1","props":{"class":"d-heading-title","id":"content-directory"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Content directory"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"prose-paragraph","props":{"class":"d-heading-description"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The "},{"type":"element","tag":"prose-a","props":{"href":"https://content.nuxtjs.org","rel":["nofollow","noopener","noreferrer"],"target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Nuxt Content module"}]},{"type":"text","value":" reads the "},{"type":"element","tag":"prose-code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"content/"}]},{"type":"text","value":" directory in your project and parses "},{"type":"element","tag":"prose-code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":".md"}]},{"type":"text","value":", "},{"type":"element","tag":"prose-code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":".yml"}]},{"type":"text","value":", "},{"type":"element","tag":"prose-code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":".csv"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"element","tag":"prose-code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":".json"}]},{"type":"text","value":" files to create a file-based CMS for your application."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"list","props":{"type":"success"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"prose-ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"prose-li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value